content:
for a more exciting Early Space Exploration experience,  Is it possible to add one or two locations and enemy npcs to the planets?

This game mode has been anticipated for a long time and although it is very good even in its raw form, it needs to be interactive for us to spend time, as you know. i see Ioki Open world update in s0 but before that, it would be great if you could give us something to shoot and interact with  in that mode.

@bunthius

@bunthius Today during the brew we got a lot of wonderful details about the ONI CSS. There are multiple districts with different architectures which is very cool. I am wondering whether the MUD and USTUR CSSs will have different districts with their distinct characteristics? 

The look of each faction CSS is very different from each other. Will that apply to the districts and habs in each faction's CSS?

Also will be find characters from different species roaming the streets in the different CSS or only the that particular Faction main species. I am guessing all but I am checking to make sure.

@Gary Sanchez (AD Veh) Hey Gary! Thanks for the sneak peek! 

Do I understand correctly that you are using lower-poly models for the ships in Fleet Command, just as was originally the case for SAGE 3D? If so, are these models comparable?

And if so, @SW4GN3R, could we see these added to the Build program asset repo? Because newer ships are missing there of course. It would be great if we could get those complete
